The paper proposes a deep neural network architecture for face alignment, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as landmark detection and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques for facial landmark detection, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its method on publicly available datasets, which could categorize it under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
